Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 1.1 percent to
4,212.52.  International Container Terminal Services Inc. (ICT)  :
The largest Philippine port operator signed an agreement with
L&T Shipbuilding Ltd. to manage and operate the Kattupalli
Container Terminal in  Tamil Nadu ,  India , according to a stock
exchange filing. The terminal, scheduled to start operations in
January 2012, will be the companyâ€™s first venture in India,
according to the statement. The stock advanced 4.4 percent to
44.95 pesos.  San Miguel Corp. (SMC)  : The largest Philippine food and
drinks company may hold a planned share sale next month,
President Ramon Ang told reporters. The stock increased 0.8
percent to 171.40 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
